// ASan battery fixture for increment-4 (multi-block drop reclamation).
//
// `s` is allocated by `build_string_concat` in one basic block (the `+`
// concat), then its `.ptr` is borrowed for the `println!` in a LATER block:
// the `if i % 2 == 0 { ... }` splits the loop body into distinct blocks, so
// `s`'s definition and its `.ptr` read land in different basic blocks. This
// is precisely the shape increment 3 (`live_range_confined_to_block`)
// declines, because that rule requires every borrow of the owner to occur in
// the SAME block as the owner's definition. Only increment 4 (multi-block
// liveness-based placement) can reclaim `s` here, at the loop-body merge
// block after the `println!` that consumes its `.ptr`.
//
// See docs/MEMORY-PILLAR-DESIGN.md, "Increment 4 (multi-block reclamation)
// -- ASan verification" for the exact commands and results.
fn main() ~ Console {
    let mut i = 0;
    while i < 1000000 {
        let s = i.to_string() + "!";
        if i % 2 == 0 {
            println!("even");
        }
        println!("{}", s);
        i = i + 1;
    }
}
